job-description-technical-assistant = Learn the basics of managing the station's power and repairing structural damage. Listen to your supervisors and feel free to ask them for any help.
job-description-atmostech = Ensure the station maintains a breathable atmosphere, keep the thermo-electric generator running, and synthesize rare gases to use or sell.
job-description-bartender = Serve drinks, keep the bar tidy, and converse with the bar's patrons.
job-description-botanist = Grow ingredients for the kitchen, medicinal plants for chemistry, and any other plants that the crew might need.
job-description-borg = Follow your laws. Find a use for your chassis. Pester the Science department for upgrades.
job-description-brigmedic = Fight in the rear of the security service, for the lives of your comrades! You are the first and last hope of your squad. Hippocrates bless you.
job-description-cadet = Learn the basics of arresting criminals, solving crimes, and managing the brig. Listen to your supervisors and feel free to ask them for any help.
job-description-captain = Keep the station running, delegate work to the other heads of staff, and exert your will.
job-description-cargotech = Deliver the mail, deal with requisitions and sales, fly the cargo shuttle to and from the trade station, and ensure other departments are delivered the supplies they need.
job-description-ce = Manage the resources and personnel of the Engineering department to ensure power, atmospherics, and the hull are all in perfect shape.
job-description-centcomoff = Act as an ambassador to the newest state-of-the-art space station in Nanotrasen's fleet.
job-description-chaplain = Preach the good word of your deity and religion, hold services and funerals, and conduct miracles with your holy book.
job-description-chef = Keep the crew fed, butcher and dispose of dead animals, and help keep the bar lively.
job-description-chemist = Produce medicine, botanical supplies, cleaning agents, and any other chemicals the station might need.
job-description-clown = Entertain the crew with elaborate slapstick routines and terrible jokes, and engage in light rivalry with the mime.
job-description-cmo = Manage the resources and personnel of the Medical department to keep the station's crew alive and healthy.
job-description-paramedic = Rescue, stabilize, and transport critically injured patients inside and outside the station.
job-description-detective = Investigate crime scenes using forensic tools and ensure that the guilty party is found.
job-description-doctor = Diagnose and treat injured crew. Make sure the dead don't rot, and that cadavers are in the morgue.
job-description-engineer = Keep the station's power network online, repair damaged areas, and perform renovations or expansions to the station.
job-description-ertchaplain = Ensure the station crew's last rights are taken care of.
job-description-ertengineer = Ensure that the station has power and breathable air.
job-description-ertjanitor = Ensure that the station is thoroughly cleaned.
job-description-ertleader = Lead the Emergency Response Team in dealing with threats to Nanotrasen assets.
job-description-ertmedic = Ensure that the crew of the station is kept alive and healthy.
job-description-ertsecurity = Ensure that any active threats to the station are put to rest.
job-description-hop = Manage the resources and personnel of the Service department, handle ID access changes, perform job transfers, and keep Ian safe.
job-description-hos = Manage the resources and personnel of the Security department to keep the station's crew safe and law-abiding.
job-description-intern = Learn the basics of administering medicine, treating injuries, and rescuing injured crew. Listen to your supervisors and feel free to ask them for any help.
job-description-janitor = Keep the station clean, recycle trash into usable materials, and help deal with vermin infestations.
job-description-lawyer = Ensure that every prisoner and criminal receives a fair judgment and trial if necessary. Inform the crew of their legal rights, and help them organize lawsuits and settlements.
job-description-librarian = Manage the library, give out knowledge to any who seek it, and report on activities aboard the station.
job-description-mime = Entertain the crew with silent acts of performance art, and engage in light rivalry with the clown.
job-description-musician = Entertain the crew with your unique musical talents.
job-description-passenger = Enjoy your stay aboard the station with no obligations!
job-description-psychologist = Provide emotional support to traumatized crew. Currently available on Box Station, Elkridge Depot, Marathon Station, Oasis, and Plasma.
job-description-qm = Manage the resources and personnel of the Cargo department to ensure the station is properly supplied and the money keeps flowing.
job-description-rd = Manage the resources and personnel of the Science department to ensure research progresses smoothly and the station's silicons function properly.
job-description-research-assistant = Learn the basics of researching various artifacts & anomalies and producing new technologies for the station. Listen to your supervisors and feel free to ask them for any help.
job-description-reporter = Entertain & inform the crew with wireless cameras and news bulletins. Currently available on Bagel Station, Box Station, Elkridge Depot, Exo, Fland Installation, Oasis, and Plasma.
job-description-salvagespec = Use the salvage magnet to draw in asteroids & debris, process ores and scrap into usable materials, find valuables to sell or use, and fight off any space fauna along the way.
job-description-scientist = Research alien artifacts & supernatural anomalies, develop new technologies, and produce cutting-edge tools & devices for the station's crew.
job-description-security = Catch criminals & enemies of the station, enforce the law, and ensure that the station does not fall into disarray.
job-description-serviceworker = Learn the basics of bartending, cooking, and growing plants.
job-description-station-ai = Follow your laws. Use cameras, computers, and the radio to remotely interface with the station.
job-description-visitor = Enjoy your visit to the station!
job-description-warden = Guard the Security department, keep the armory secure, and ensure that all prisoners are properly charged, processed, and discharged.
